response.overview: Some memories fade, some are gone completely. Some pieces I laid to rest and others lay bleeding. Torn, empty, a bug caught in my veil. A bell rings somewhere far away, I empty you of me. I took what was left and the rest I burned in the alley in my wedding dress. Filmed in July of 2025 on lək̓ wəŋən lands. Thank you to my collaborator Claire Abercrombie. It wouldn’t have been possible without her. One day we’ll shoot the rest.
response.title: Never Land
